                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d197">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Chinese Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chinese Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-04-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 17, 1905</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 61.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your note of the 13th instant, in which you embody the reply of the Secretary of
                    Commerce and Labor to my protest against the taking of a census by the bureau of
                    immigration while negotiations for a treaty are pending involving this very
                    subject.</p>
                <p>Secretary Metcalf’s letter confirms my impression that there has been no
                    legislation of Congress requiring such action, and, as it is plainly within his
                    administrative control, I must confidently believe that he will not further push
                    the matter of the census till the negotiations are concluded. I am gratified to
                    note that the action of the bureau of immigration as set forth in the
                    Secretary’s letter is not recognized by you as a sufficient answer to my
                    protest.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Chentung Liang-Cheng.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
